9:
What's wrong, Trista? Should we double
back and buy the Eau de Cherub
after all?
13:
That junk?! No! More importantly,
have a look at this...
18:
Adventures Weekly. "Forge Your Path by
Intuition: An interview with Levy Gracia."
21:
You brought that magazine with you
all the way here?
25:
This has to be it. I have plenty of
knowledge; I've done plenty of analysis.
So I must lack intuition...
28:
Intuition, huh? I suppose it is crucial
at certain moments.
42:
A tremor! The Kaleidoscope is shifting!
If we don't hurry, we'll be swallowed
whole!
51: Th-this can't be real! We gotta scram!
56:
If my intuition is correct... This is
a hallucination.
60:
What are you saying, Trista?!
You know how many adventurers
have gone missing!
67:
There haven't been any abnormal
shifts in the shallow levels for the past
few decades!
69:
Besides, the shifts are always
accompanied by signs. What signs
have we seen?
72:
N-none... But, but... At this rate,
everyone's gonna—
75:
...Fine. You have our faith. Your
knowledge trumps our judgment.
78:
Is it even possible for everyone
to experience the same hallucination?
81: I can't speak to that, but—
88:
I knew it—it's morgana pollen!
You, have you seen any yellow
flowers around?
90:
They were blooming everywhere.
I thought they were medicinal,
so I picked a few...
97:
They're dangerous weeds, said to
bring on terrible visions with a single
sniff. I bet that's what's happened here.
98:
However, the effects don't last long.
If this really is a morgana-induced
hallucination, it should wear off soon.
112:
Had we fled towards the exit, we would
have plunged into the abyss.
122:
If that tremor had been a real shift,
I don't know what I would have done.
What if I couldn't have
protected you all?
126:
Trista. There are going to be many
situations where intuition alone won't
save you.
128:
Your knowledge and analytical
prowess are your strengths.
THEY are what protect your friends.
131:
We need that on our team.
We're grateful for you.
136:
Light's right! I was panicking like crazy,
but you read the situation perfectly!
140:
You are a valuable member of
our team, Trista.
146: Thanks! You can always count on me!
